snippet: Hasna Aitboulahcen once liked to drink, smoke and stay out late. She spent her last days in a St.-Denis hide-out for Islamist militants.
abstract: Neighbors and acquaintances of Hasna Aitboulahcen, woman who was killed in nighttime raid on apartment in Paris suburb of St -Denis, describe how she went from being onetime wild child to devotee of Islamic State; authorities say Aitboulahcen was first person to open fire on police raiding apartment.

byline.contributor: Nabih Bulos and Elian Peltier contributed reporting from Paris.

lead_paragraph: Hasna Aitboulahcen once liked to drink, smoke and stay out late. She spent her last days in a St.-Denis hide-out for Islamist militants.

headline.main: For Woman Dead in French Police Raid, Unlikely Path to Terror
headline.print_headline: Woman Killed in French Police Raid Had Unlikely Path to Extremism
